<figureCitation box="[151,226,1222,1247]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1887,1909]" captionTargetBox="[169,1405,195,1847]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[169,1405,195,1847]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 6. Spotted male metasomas. (A) Perdita arenaria (paratype, UCRC 166022; Imperial Co., CA). (B) P. frontalis (BBSL 813851; Imperial Co., CA). (C) P. maculosa (BBSL 277846; Clark Co., NV). (D) P. nuttalliae (Paratype, BBSL 816190; Harney Co., OR). (E) P. sycorax (paratype, 37225; Emery Co., UT). (F) P. titania (paratype, UCRC 166000; Imperial Co., CA). (G) P. wasbaueri (BBSL 842195; San Bernardino Co., CA). (H) P. yanegai (paratype, UCRC 166011; Riverside Co., CA). All scale bars 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253092/files/figure.png" pageId="77" pageNumber="78">Figs. 6</figureCitation>
